						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in Vishṇu temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1203, Uttarāyaṇa-Sankranti.</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of a pillar to the temple of Śri-Bhōgīśvara Mahādēva of Oṅgōlu and also 15 cows by Kannama-Reddi and Tammi-Reddi for the merit of their parents.</p>						

